JOHANNESBURG - The South African Police Service (SAPS) and acting police commissioner Kgomotso Phahlane will brief Parliament on Wednesday on police operations during the festive season and crime statistics.The briefing comes a week after the head of the Independent Police Investigative Directorate (Ipid), Robert McBride, accused Phahlane of lying about an investigation.He also claimed that police were involved in a drugs syndicate at OR Tambo International Airport.The Gauteng police commissioner is also expected to brief Parliament on violent protests. eNCA